SIMPLE: bolting
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bolting
<hw>Bolt"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A darting away; a starting off or
aside.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bolting</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bolting
<hw>Bolt"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sifting, as of flour
or meal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A private arguing of cases for
practice by students, as in the Inns of Court.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bolting cloth</b></col>, <cd>wire, hair, silk, or other
sieve cloth of different degrees of fineness; -- used by millers for
sifting flour.</cd> <au>McElrath.</au> -- <col><b>Bolting
hutch</b></col>, <cd>a bin or tub for the bolted flour or meal</cd>;
(<mark>fig.</mark>) <cd>a receptacle.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boltonite</ent>⟦br⟧
